      • getImmediateCoordinates

        public int[][] getImmediateCoordinates(Entity entity)
        Gets the immediate coordinates within a one space radius of a given entity.
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity for which we are looking for the surrounding coordinates of.
        Returns:
        A 2D array containing 8 coordinates surrounding a location. Each two-element array within the returned array represents a the X and Y coordinate of a location. the coordinates return in the following pattern (where n represents the location given): 0 1 2 7 n 3 6 5 4

      • getExtendedCoordinates

        public int[][] getExtendedCoordinates(Entity entity)
        Gets the extended coordinates surrounding a given entity within a six space radius.
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity for which we are finding the surrounding coordinates of.
        Returns:
        A 2D array containing the extended coordinates surrounding the specified entity within a six space radius. Each two-element array within the returned array represents a the X and Y coordinate of a location. The coordinates will return in the following order: 167 120 121 122 123 124 125 126 127 128 129 130 131 166 119 80 81 82 83 84 85 86 87 88 89 132 165 118 79 48 49 50 51 52 53 54 55 90 133 164 117 78 47 24 25 26 27 28 29 56 91 134 163 116 77 46 8 9 10 11 12 30 57 92 135 162 115 76 45 23 0 1 2 13 31 58 93 136 161 114 75 44 22 7 ENTITY 3 14 32 59 94 137 160 113 74 43 21 6 5 4 15 33 60 95 138 159 112 73 42 20 19 18 17 16 34 61 96 139 158 111 72 41 40 39 38 37 36 35 62 97 140 157 110 71 70 69 68 67 66 65 64 63 98 141 156 109 108 107 106 105 104 103 102 101 100 99 142 155 154 153 152 151 150 149 148 147 146 145 144 143

                                       int y,
                                       int animalType)
        Checks if there is food within one space away from a certain location given the coordinates and the predator's type.
        Parameters:
        x - The x coordinate of the location we are investigating.
        y - The y coordinate of the location we are investigating.
        animalType - The type of the animal that will be eating the food. 1 stands for herbivore and 2 stands for carnivore.
        Returns:
